      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLASH GORDON (1) had been going along well winning a Other three back then placing at this track before missing the frame latest when sixth (18.34) at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Will find this more suitable and can atone. ASTON JIMENA (8) was below best latest but did hit the frame in quick time two back when second (17.75) at this track in a Other. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can improve sharply here. TRIAL KING (4) copped a check in the run last time and never threatened when sixth (18.35) in a Grade 3/4/5 at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Key player if finds best. BULSARA (2) is a last-start placegetter out of the same box - worth considering.",
